		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Turbo code</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>In <a href="/wiki/Electrical_engineering" title="Electrical engineering">electrical engineering</a> and <a href="/wiki/Digital_communications" title="Digital communications" class="mw-redirect">digital communications</a>, <b>turbo codes</b> (originally in French <i>Turbocodes</i>) are a class of high-performance <a href="/wiki/Error-correcting_code" title="Error-correcting code" class="mw-redirect">error correction codes</a> developed in 1993 which are finding use in <a href="/wiki/Deep_space" title="Deep space" class="mw-redirect">deep space</a> <a href="/wiki/Satellite" title="Satellite">satellite</a> <a href="/wiki/Telecommunication" title="Telecommunication">communications</a> and other applications where designers seek to achieve maximal information transfer over a limited-bandwidth communication link in the presence of data-corrupting noise.</p>
